<subSubSection id="C319656D2C12DF16FF0985A3675FFC37" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36E62C12DF16FF0985A3675FFC37" blockId="1.[151,1437,669,1416]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF0985A3635BFD34" bold="true" box="[151,274,669,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FE8585A363C1FD34" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[283,392,669,695]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FE8585A363C1FD34" box="[283,392,669,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the following combination of characters: 1. Anatergite bare; 2. Scutellum with impressed rim; 3. Mystax with about six remarkably stout macrosetae placed in a triangular area near the lower facial margin; 4. Scape and pedicel bearing conspicuous ventral and lateral macrosetae (Fig. 207, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FA8585DB67C6FC83" author="Hull, F. M." box="[1307,1423,741,768]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 907" refId="ref14896" refString="Hull, F. M. (1962) Robber Flies of the world: The genera of the Family Asilidae. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 224 (1 - 2), 1 - 907. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.224" type="journal article" year="1962">Hull 1962</bibRefCitation>
); 5. Apical third of wing darkened by dense microtrichia (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FC8B84376113FCA0" box="[789,858,777,803]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,1287,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[168,1419,1281,1739]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wing venation. Regasilus huiracocha sp. nov. Paratype. Abbreviations. al, alula; bm, basal medial cell; br, basal radial cell; C, costal vein; CuA,anterior branch of cubital vein; cua, anterior cubital cell; CuP, posterior branch of cubital vein; cup, posterior cubital cell; d, discal cell; fal vn, false vein; M 1, first branch of media; m 1, first medial cell; M 2, second branch of media; m 2, second medial cell; M 3, third branch of media; m 3, third medial cell; M 4, fourth branch of media; m 4, fourth medial cell; m–cu, medial–cubital crossvein; m–m, medial crossvein; R 1, anterior branch of radius; r 1, first radial cell; R 2+3, second branch of radius; r 2+3, second + third radial cell; R 4, upper branch of third branch of radius; r 4, fourth radial cell; R, third branch 4+5 of radius;R , lower branch of third branch of radius; r , fifth radial cell; r–m, radial–medial crossvein; Sc, subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4315671/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); 6. Fore femora without prominent macrosetae; 7. Eighth sternite in males bearing a dense and conspicuous band of macrosetae apically (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FB1E84136693FCC4" box="[1152,1242,813,839]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,181,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1489]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Regasilus aiapaec sp. nov. Male holotype. A. Habitus lateral; B. Terminalia, lateral view; C. Wing; D. Terminalia, dorsal view; E. Phallus, lateral and dorsal views; F. Gonocoxite and gonostylus; G. Hypandrium. Abbreviations. d, discal cell; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; epd, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; goncx apod, gonocoxal apodeme; gonst, gonostylus; hypd, hypandrium; M 1, first branch of media; M 2, second branch of media; M 3, third branch of media; M 4, fourth branch of media; m–cu, medial–cubital crossvein; R 1, anterior branch of radius; R 2+3, second branch of radius; R 4, upper branch of third branch of radius; R, third branch of radius; R, lower branch of third branch of radius; r–m, radial–medial crossvein" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4327255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4327255/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); 8. Hypandrium with a posterior and central excision (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FDA6846F60C5FCE8" box="[568,652,849,875]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,184,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[162,1426,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Regasilus strigarius Curran, 1931. Male from Baños.A. Habitus lateral; B. Terminalia, dorsal view; C. Terminalia, lateral view; D. Phallus, lateral and dorsal views; E. Gonocoxite and gonostylus; F. Hypandrium. Abbreviations. cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; epand, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; goncx apod, gonocoxal apodeme; gonst, gonostylus; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; st 8, eighth sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4315673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); 9. Female ovipositor apubescent and laterally compressed from sixth abdominal segment (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FEE1844B639FFC13" box="[383,470,885,912]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,345,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-91@6.[157,1430,345,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Regasilus aiapaec sp. nov. Female paratype. A. Habitus lateral; B. Terminalia, ovipositor, lateral view; C. Furca and spermathecae. Abbreviations. ar, arms of furca; cap duct, capsular duct; cerc, cercus; com duct, common duct; exp duct, expulsory duct; f apod, furcal apodeme; med scl, median sclerite (remnant of tergite 9); spmth, spermathecae; tg 6, tg 7, tg 8, tg 10, abdominal tergites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4315677/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
); 10. Common duct long, with three strongly attenuated and apically-coiled spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FF5284A7636AFC37" box="[204,291,921,948]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,345,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-91@6.[157,1430,345,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Regasilus aiapaec sp. nov. Female paratype. A. Habitus lateral; B. Terminalia, ovipositor, lateral view; C. Furca and spermathecae. Abbreviations. ar, arms of furca; cap duct, capsular duct; cerc, cercus; com duct, common duct; exp duct, expulsory duct; f apod, furcal apodeme; med scl, median sclerite (remnant of tergite 9); spmth, spermathecae; tg 6, tg 7, tg 8, tg 10, abdominal tergites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4315677/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); and 11. Median sclerite at posterior end of furca (remnant of tergite 9) present (
<figureCitation id="13382A632C12DF16FB2F84A76740FC37" box="[1201,1289,921,948]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,345,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-91@6.[157,1430,345,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Regasilus aiapaec sp. nov. Female paratype. A. Habitus lateral; B. Terminalia, ovipositor, lateral view; C. Furca and spermathecae. Abbreviations. ar, arms of furca; cap duct, capsular duct; cerc, cercus; com duct, common duct; exp duct, expulsory duct; f apod, furcal apodeme; med scl, median sclerite (remnant of tergite 9); spmth, spermathecae; tg 6, tg 7, tg 8, tg 10, abdominal tergites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315677" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4315677/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C319656D2C12DF16FF598483664EFA0B" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBC36E62C12DF16FF598483664EFA0B" blockId="1.[151,1437,669,1416]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF5984836306FC54" bold="true" box="[199,335,957,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Comments.</emphasis>
From examination of specimens of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FCBF8483618BFC54" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1866" box="[801,962,957,983]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Glaphyropyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FCBF8483618BFC54" box="[801,962,957,983]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Glaphyropyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group housed in MZUC–UCCC, as well as the illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FE1784DF60F2FC7F" author="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N." box="[393,699,993,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="11 - 33" refId="ref14454" refString="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N. (1995) The American genera of Asilidae (Diptera): Keys for identification with an atlas of female spermathecae and other morphological details. IX. 4. Subfamily Asilinae Leach- Glaphyropyga group with the proposal of two new genera and a catalogue of the Neotropical species. Boletin de la Sociedad de Biologia de Concepcion, 66, 11 - 33." type="journal article" year="1995">Artigas &amp; Papavero (1995)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FD6C84DF61D0FC78" author="Artigas, J. N." box="[754,921,993,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref14371" refString="Artigas, J. N. (1971) Las estructuras quitinizadas de la spermatheca y funda del pene de los Asilidos y su valor sistematico a traves del estudio por taxonomia numerica. Gayana (Zoologia), 18, 1 - 106." type="journal article" year="1971">Artigas (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FC3B84DF665BFC78" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[933,1042,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FC3B84DF665BFC78" box="[933,1042,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FAF784DC601CFB9C" authority="Lynch Arribalzaga, 1880" authorityName="Lynch Arribalzaga" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Leptoharpacticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FAF784DC6378FB9C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Leptoharpacticus</emphasis>
Lynch Arribálzaga, 1880
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FD0E833B6632FBA3" authority="Artigas &amp; Papavero, 1995" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Papavero" authorityYear="1995" box="[656,1147,1029,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Megalometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FD0E833B610FFB9C" box="[656,838,1029,1055]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megalometopon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FCD1833B6632FBA3" author="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N." box="[847,1147,1029,1056]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="11 - 33" refId="ref14454" refString="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N. (1995) The American genera of Asilidae (Diptera): Keys for identification with an atlas of female spermathecae and other morphological details. IX. 4. Subfamily Asilinae Leach- Glaphyropyga group with the proposal of two new genera and a catalogue of the Neotropical species. Boletin de la Sociedad de Biologia de Concepcion, 66, 11 - 33." type="journal article" year="1995">Artigas &amp; Papavero, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FF0983146394FBC0" authority="Artigas, 1970" authorityName="Artigas" authorityYear="1970" box="[151,477,1065,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Megametopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF098314637EFBC0" box="[151,311,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megametopon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FEDE83176394FBC0" author="Artigas, J. N." box="[320,477,1065,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 474" refId="ref14344" refString="Artigas, J. N. (1970) Los asilidos de Chile (Diptera-Asilidae). Gayana, Zoologia, 17, 1 - 474." type="journal article" year="1970">Artigas, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a junior homonym), since these three genera share features such as the fore femora without prominent macrosetae, eighth sternite with an apical band of macrosetae in males, presence of a median sclerite at posterior end of furca in females, and a long common duct with three strongly attenuated and apicallycoiled spermathecae. Although 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FE6883AB60F3FB2C" authorityName="Lynch Arribalzaga" authorityYear="1880" box="[502,698,1173,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Leptoharpacticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FE6883AB60F3FB2C" box="[502,698,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Leptoharpacticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguishable owing to its shallow facial gibbosity, plus other differences, to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FD9383876033FB50" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[525,634,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FD9383876033FB50" box="[525,634,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FD5A83876133FB50" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Papavero" authorityYear="1995" box="[708,890,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Megalometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FD5A83876133FB50" box="[708,890,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megalometopon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more difficult, since the diagnosis given for 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FF0983E3634DFB74" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,260,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF0983E3634DFB74" box="[151,260,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein also keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FD8C83E36081FB74" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Papavero" authorityYear="1995" box="[530,712,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Megalometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FD8C83E36081FB74" box="[530,712,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megalometopon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for character 3. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FC6483E366F9FB74" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Papavero" authorityYear="1995" box="[1018,1200,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Megalometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FC6483E366F9FB74" box="[1018,1200,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megalometopon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the mystacal macrosetae are uniform, nevertheless some other features of this genus are observed in the variation range of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FF28821B636AFABC" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[182,291,1317,1343]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF28821B636AFABC" box="[182,291,1317,1343]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described in this work. Therefore, the relationship between these two genera needs to be reevaluated, since 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FF4882776330FAE0" author="Artigas, J. N." box="[214,377,1353,1379]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref14371" refString="Artigas, J. N. (1971) Las estructuras quitinizadas de la spermatheca y funda del pene de los Asilidos y su valor sistematico a traves del estudio por taxonomia numerica. Gayana (Zoologia), 18, 1 - 106." type="journal article" year="1971">Artigas (1971)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B172C12DF16FE3382776092FAE7" author="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N." box="[429,731,1353,1380]" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" pagination="11 - 33" refId="ref14454" refString="Artigas, J. N. &amp; Papavero, N. (1995) The American genera of Asilidae (Diptera): Keys for identification with an atlas of female spermathecae and other morphological details. IX. 4. Subfamily Asilinae Leach- Glaphyropyga group with the proposal of two new genera and a catalogue of the Neotropical species. Boletin de la Sociedad de Biologia de Concepcion, 66, 11 - 33." type="journal article" year="1995">Artigas &amp; Papavero (1995)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FCFA82776653FAE0" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Papavero" authorityYear="1995" box="[868,1050,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Megalometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FCFA82776653FAE0" box="[868,1050,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Megalometopon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without examining any specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D652C12DF16FF288253636AFA04" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1931" box="[182,291,1389,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Regasilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAF42C12DF16FF288253636AFA04" box="[182,291,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="222">Regasilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, raising the possibility that these genera are subjective synonyms.
</paragraph>
